Grey Council is a guild of people that role play in the world of Norrath to enjoy their leisure time. They are also responsible for helping others as best they can by respecting others and following the rules set forth by the officers of Grey Council. Members of Grey Council (inductees and full members) must always be respectful of other players, be generous by nature and willing to work out any issues that might arise as best they can.
	<br><br><center><img src="images/bullet.gif" border="0"></center><br><br>
	Respect comes from treating people as you would like to be treated: helping someone that has lost their way, died to some unfortunate accident or just by giving them a simple spirit of wolf or portal if you can.
	<br><br><center><img src="images/bullet.gif" border="0"></center><br><br>
	A GC raid is two or more groups of GC with the majority of those 2 groups GC members.
	<br><br><center><img src="images/bullet.gif" border="0"></center><br><br>
	Being generous can take on many forms. If you gain a item you cannot use or is 'lower quality' than yours, you give it to active main GC member. On GC Raids, active mains always get looting preference over Alts. If you win a item on a GC raid and the item is on an alt of yours, loan it to an active main GC member if it is a upgrade for them until they can attain better. Any items given to you by a GC member that upgrades a item you have currently cannot be traded without first trying to see if someone else in GC can use. You also pass down any items you upgrade (no longer need) to an active main GC member.
	<br><br><center><img src="images/bullet.gif" border="0"></center><br><br>
	On most major raids GC uses a merit based loot system as determined by the raid leader - applicants or new guild members may not be considered for items as heavily as full members.
	<br><br><center><img src="images/bullet.gif" border="0"></center><br><br>
	Epic quest assistance, officially organized by the guild and its leaders, is not given until the member reaches full member status and is level 55 or higher. Certain cases might arise where level will not be taken into account (almost completed quest, very useful to guild such as cleric epic/etc). There are several reasons for this, one of which is there are just far too many people in GC to work on everyone's epic item without some sort of limit. Level limits will ensure that the player will be most effective with his/her epic weapon in guild raids.
	<br><br><center><img src="images/bullet.gif" border="0"></center><br><br>
	Grey Council cannot always provide everyone a group. This is the responsibility of the member. If no groups have an opening, create one!
	<br><br><center><img src="images/bullet.gif" border="0"></center><br><br>
	We do NOT sell to guildmembers.
	<br><br><center><img src="images/bullet.gif" border="0"></center><br><br>
	Grey Council's goal is to enjoy Everquest. We're not about killing the biggest mobs repeatedly to gain items as quickly as we can. We explore new areas as we become capable, slay beasts when the desire arises and help members complete their epic quests as we can.-->
